                <head>Virginia State Agricultural Society</head>
                <origin/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <commentary/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Complains that the Virginia State Agricultural Society will not be holding
                    another fair in Richmond.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>The Opposition Meeting</head>
                <origin>The Vindicator</origin>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <commentary/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Addresses a request from the Vindicator for more information about the
                    Opposition's position. Vindicator claims that the Opposition wants to nominate
                    John Minor Botts for President; Spectator and Opposition say no.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Important Decision</head>
                <origin/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <commentary/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Sanger</ln>
                        <fn>Jacob</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Baldwin</ln>
                        <fn>John</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Imboden</ln>
                        <fn>John</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Michie</ln>
                        <fn>Thomas</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Stuart</ln>
                        <fn>Alexander</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Lyons</ln>
                        <fn>James</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Court of Appeals has upheld judgement in Sanger vs. Central Railroad
                    Company. Augusta Court had awarded Sanger damages for injuries sustained in a
                    train derailment in 1856. This case was the first time that a Virginia court had
                    settled liability on the railroad.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Railroad Dividends</head>
                <origin/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <commentary/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Dividend of 2.5% was paid on Virginia Central Railroad. Augusta County will
                    clear $1000.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="l">
                <column>5</column>
                <head>For the Spectator</head>
                <origin/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Justice; August 27, 1859</trailer>
                <commentary/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Complains about the collection of taxes and tithables. The primary
                    complaint is that it is too easy to cheat on taxes, and that the commissioner
                    isn't doing anything to stop such evasion. He needs to do something to remedy
                    the long list of delinquents, maybe prohibit non-payers from voting.</summary>
            </div>
